## Development Commands

```bash
# Root (runs both client and server concurrently)
npm run dev

# Client only
npm run dev --prefix client        # next dev
npm run build --prefix client      # next build
npm run lint --prefix client       # eslint

# Server only
npm run dev --prefix server        # tsx watch src/index.ts
npm run build --prefix server      # tsc
npm run start --prefix server      # node dist/index.js
npm run seed --prefix server       # tsx prisma/seed.ts (bootstrap admin + settings)
```

## Key Conventions

### General
- **TypeScript everywhere**: all code (client and server) must be written in TypeScript with strict mode enabled — no plain `.js` files, no `any` unless absolutely unavoidable
- **Documentation lookup**: always use the **Context7 MCP** (`resolve-library-id` → `get-library-docs`) to fetch up-to-date documentation before using or advising on any library, framework, or tool — even well-known ones (Next.js, React, Prisma, Tailwind, Express, Zod, etc.)

### Backend
- **Modular structure**: each feature lives in `server/src/modules/<feature>/` with `service` and `validation` files; **routes** may be one or more routers (e.g. `exercise.routes.ts`, `folder.routes.ts`) mounted from `app.ts` under `/api/<segment>`
- **Validation**: Zod schemas validate request bodies via `validate()` middleware
- **Error handling**: throw `AppError` subclasses (`ConflictError`, `UnauthorizedError`) — caught by global `errorHandler`; `ZodError` → 400 with `details` (Zod 4 exposes issues on `err.issues`, not `errors`)
- **Health**: `GET /api/health` — lightweight status JSON for uptime checks
- **Email (invitations)**: `server/src/lib/mail.ts` — Nodemailer SMTP from env (`SMTP_HOST`, `SMTP_PORT`, `SMTP_USER`, `SMTP_PASS`, optional `SMTP_SECURE`, `MAIL_FROM`). When fully configured, `POST /api/admin/invite` sends the register link after creating the row; response always includes `inviteLink` plus `emailSent` / `emailError` for the UI. `CLIENT_URL` builds the invite URL (same origin the user should open in the browser)
- **Auth**: Better Auth handles `/api/auth/*` via `toNodeHandler`; protected routes use `authenticate` middleware which reads the session cookie via `auth.api.getSession()`; `req.user` is `{ instructorId, email, role }`; feature routes mount at `/api/<module>` (e.g. `/api/exercises`, `/api/admin`)
- **Public registration helpers**: `app.ts` exposes `/api/signup-status` and `/api/invite/verify` (query `token`) for the register page; invitation creation and listing live under `/api/admin/*`
- **Admin plugin**: Better Auth admin plugin (`defaultRole: "INSTRUCTOR"`, `adminRole: "ADMIN"`) provides `/api/auth/admin/*` endpoints (listUsers, banUser, unbanUser, setRole); custom admin routes at `/api/admin/*` use `authenticate` + `requireAdmin` middleware
- **Roles**: `Role` enum (`ADMIN` | `INSTRUCTOR`); default is `INSTRUCTOR`; admin guard via `requireAdmin` middleware
- **Prisma**: client imported from `src/lib/prisma.ts`; generated output at `src/generated/prisma`
- **Soft deletes**: `deletedAt` field on applicable models; soft-deleting an exercise also removes its Cloudinary assets and `ExerciseImage` rows
- **Image uploads (hybrid flow)**: images are uploaded to Cloudinary `temp/` folder via `POST /api/uploads/temp` (multer, 5 MB limit, JPEG/PNG/WebP); on exercise create/update, `publicIds[]` in the request body triggers promotion from `temp/` to `exercises/<exerciseId>/` via `cloudinary.uploader.rename` with UUID-based collision-resistant naming and all-or-nothing compensation; `DELETE /api/uploads/temp/:publicId` removes temp images; `PATCH /api/exercises/:id/images/reorder` reorders saved images; an hourly `node-cron` job deletes temp images older than 6 hours
- **Express type augmentation**: `server/src/types/express.d.ts` adds `imagePublicIds?: string[]` to `Request` via declaration merging; an inline middleware in exercise routes extracts `publicIds` from the body before Zod validation so schemas stay unchanged
- **Exercise progressions**: `Exercise.progressionOfId` points to an easier variation (self-referential FK). Service walks backward to root then forward for a linear chain. **`GET /api/exercises/:id/progression-chain`** returns `{ id, name, level }[]` from root to harder steps. **`PATCH /api/exercises/:id/progression`** body `{ progressionOfId: string | null }` updates only progression; **`POST/PATCH /api/exercises`** accept optional `progressionOfId` on create/update (Zod in `exercise.validation.ts`). Cycle prevention is enforced in **`ExerciseForm`** on edit (blocked parent IDs from the chain); consider hardening in the service if API clients multiply.
- **Exercise layers**: `ExerciseLayer` model stores ordered content blocks (`order`, `content`, `isFinisher`) per exercise; create/update endpoints accept `layers: { content, order?, isFinisher? }[]` — service replaces all layers atomically via `deleteMany` + `createMany`
- **Dropdown options API**: `server/src/modules/dropdowns/` — **`GET /api/dropdowns/:categoryKey`** returns options (global + instructor-specific) for a category; **`POST /api/dropdowns/:categoryKey`** creates an instructor-scoped custom option. `server/prisma/seed.ts` seeds categories with keys: `orientation`, `direction_faced`, `movement_type`, `equipment`, `machine_setup`, `spinal_movement`, `chain_type`, `joint_loading`, `class_type`, `class_style`
- **Extended exercise fields**: `Exercise` has optional string fields: `orientation`, `directionFaced`, `movementType`, `springs`, `machineSetup`, `transitionCues`, `cueing`; **`equipment`** and **`chainType`** are `String[]` (multiselect, default `[]`); **`spinalMovement`** and **`jointLoading`** are `String[]`; optional **`progressionNotes`** and **`regressionNotes`** (`String?`) for in-exercise progression/regression copy. Form uses dropdowns, checkboxes, and text inputs; detail page renders array fields as badges where applicable

### Frontend
- **"use client"** directive on interactive pages and layout components
- **Auth gate**: `AppLayout` redirects unauthenticated users to `/login`; `AuthProvider` wraps Better Auth's `useSession()` hook
- **App shell**: `AppLayout` renders `Sidebar` + scrollable `main` only (no top bar). **Sidebar** — fixed mobile menu button; drawer on small screens, rail on `md+`; nav links in a scrollable middle; **account menu pinned to the bottom** (`DropdownMenu`, opens upward) with avatar, name/email, and **Log out** (`useAuth().logout` then `router.replace("/login")`). **Main** uses `p-4 pt-14` on small screens so content clears the hamburger; `md:p-6 md:pt-6` from `md` up.
- **Auth client**: `authClient` from `@/lib/auth-client` — provides `signIn.email()`, `signUp.email()`, `signOut()`, `useSession()`, plus `admin.*` methods via `adminClient` plugin
- **Roles**: `useAuth()` exposes `isAdmin` boolean and `instructor.role`; sidebar conditionally renders admin navigation; admin routes under `(dashboard)/admin/` have a layout guard redirecting non-admins
- **Path alias**: `@/*` maps to `./src/*`
- **Forms**: use **React Hook Form** with **`zodResolver`** from `@hookform/resolvers/zod` — `useForm({ resolver: zodResolver(schema), ... })` and Zod schemas under **`@/lib/validation/*`** (`auth-schemas.ts` for **`/login`**, **`/register`**, and **admin invite** via **`adminInviteFormSchema`**; `exercise-form-schema.ts` + **`buildExerciseFormDefaults`** for **`ExerciseForm`**); align with server Zod where practical. **`ExerciseForm`** also uses **`useFieldArray`** for `layers`, **`Controller`** for shadcn **`Select`** and **`BulletTextarea`**, **`register`** / **`useWatch`** / **`setValue`** / **`getValues`** for other fields; image list (dropzone, reorder, temp `publicIds`) stays in **local React state** outside RHF; **`reset`** when `exercise?.id` changes on edit. **Admin invite** (`admin/users/page.tsx` dialog): same stack — **`Controller`** + shadcn **`Select`** for role (styling aligned with **`ExerciseForm`** selects), **`register`** for email, inline **`errors.*`** + **`aria-invalid`** / **`border-destructive`** like exercise form fields.
- **UI components**: use **shadcn/ui** for all UI primitives and patterns that shadcn provides; import from `@/components/ui/*`. Build feature-specific composites under `components/<feature>/` (and `components/layout/`) rather than reimplementing primitives inline
- **Theming / colors**: prefer shadcn **semantic tokens** (`bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `text-muted-foreground`, `text-destructive`, `border-border`, `bg-card`, etc.) over hardcoded Tailwind palette utilities (e.g. `bg-gray-900`, `text-red-500`) so light/dark and theme tweaks stay consistent
- **Component layout**: shell in `components/layout/`; dashboard composites in `components/dashboard/`; domain UI in `components/<domain>/`; shared hooks in `hooks/`
- **API calls**: use the `api` helper from `@/lib/api` for generic requests; prefer typed modules in `@/services/*` (e.g. `admin-api`, `exercise-api`) for feature endpoints — all use `credentials: "include"` via the shared client; base URL from `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL`
- **`exerciseApi`** (`@/services/exercise-api`): typed helpers for exercises — `getExercises`, `getExerciseById`, `createExercise`, `updateExercise`, `deleteExercise`, `setProgression`, `getProgressionChain`, folder CRUD, image add/delete/reorder, temp upload/delete. **`SaveExerciseBody`** includes optional `progressionOfId`, `progressionNotes`, `regressionNotes`, `equipment: string[]`, `chainType: string[]`, and `layers: { content, order?, isFinisher? }[]`. Exercise pages and forms should use this module rather than ad-hoc `api.get`/`patch` for `/exercises/*`.
- **`dropdownApi`** (`@/services/dropdown-api`): `getOptions(categoryKey)` and `createOption(categoryKey, label)`. **`useDropdownOptions(key)`** hook fetches and caches options for a category; form selects consume it.
- **Exercise progression UI**: **`ProgressionChainViewer`** (`components/exercises/progression-chain-viewer.tsx`) on the exercise detail page shows Level 1 → harder steps (responsive layout, current exercise highlighted); skips rendering when the chain has fewer than two steps. **`ExerciseForm`** includes `progressionOfId` in the save payload (defaults to `"none"` → `null`). The inline **"Easier version (progression)"** `Select` is **commented out** in `exercise-form.tsx`; instructors can still change progression via **`exerciseApi.setProgression`** / **`PATCH /api/exercises/:id/progression`**, or restore/rewire the block with **`Controller`**. On edit, **`getProgressionChain`** still feeds **blocked parent IDs** so a disallowed easier parent cannot be submitted if the picker is re-enabled. Stale `progressionOfId` after a soft-deleted parent is handled on the API side; the commented UI described orphan restore/clear options when active.
- **Exercise library page** (`exercises/page.tsx`): unified `exercise-library-header` card (title, live stats, "New folder" + "New exercise" buttons, embedded search bar, folder `Select` dropdown with per-folder counts, inline Rename/Delete buttons when a folder is selected) + `exercise-list` grid. No separate sidebar or toolbar component — all controls live in the header. `exercise-list` shows a "filtered-empty" state with a "Clear filters" action when a folder/search yields zero results but the library is non-empty. Search queries `name` + `description` only (backend `contains`, case-insensitive). Folder management (create/rename/delete) via `folder-dialog` triggered from header buttons. **`ExerciseLibraryPagination`** (`components/exercises/exercise-library-pagination.tsx`): shown under the grid on **`/exercises`** as a **placeholder** bar (first/prev/page numbers/next/last) until list API paging is wired; pass **`page`**, **`totalPages`**, **`onPageChange`**, optional **`loading`** / **`ariaLabel`** for **controlled** mode — used on **`/admin/users`** so pagination matches the same UI.
- **Admin users page** (`admin/users/page.tsx`): UX mirrors the exercise library — outer **`space-y-6`** + rounded page shell, single header card (title, live stats, **Invite user**, **`useDebounce`** email search with clear control), directory vs filtered **empty states** (same intent as `exercise-list`), user table + **`ExerciseLibraryPagination`** (controlled). Listing uses Better Auth **`authClient.admin.listUsers`** with pagination + optional email search. Invitations via **`adminApi.invite`**. Row actions: details sheet, role change, ban/unban via admin plugin.
- **Exercise image dropzone**: `exercise-form.tsx` uses `react-dropzone` (`useDropzone`) for drag-and-drop image uploads to temp storage; saved and temp images are unified into a single sortable list with HTML5 drag-to-reorder; both saved and temp images can be deleted from the form; temp images include `publicIds[]` on form submit
- **Exercise layer UI**: form renders dynamic layer rows (add/remove); each row is labeled `Layer 1`, `Layer 2`, … Only the **last** row can be marked **Finisher** via a checkbox (`ExerciseLayer.isFinisher`). Adding a layer clears any prior finisher flag; finisher rows can show a badge and distinct styling. **`getLayerStepTitle`** in `@/lib/exercise-layer-labels` returns the layer label only (`Layer N`, no automatic finisher wording).
- **`BulletTextarea`** (`components/exercises/bullet-textarea.tsx`): used in **`ExerciseForm`** for each layer row `content`, plus description, starting position, cueing, progression notes, and regression notes. Bullets are literal `•` in the stored string (no list sub-model). **Enter** inserts `\n• `; **Shift+Enter** inserts a newline only; **Add •** inserts `• ` at the line start when allowed; **`bulletsEnabled={false}`** renders a plain shadcn `Textarea` without bullet behavior. Optional **`label`**, **`toolbarEndSlot`** (e.g. remove layer), and **`data-bullet-textarea-toolbar`** on the toolbar group preserve focus/UX when tabbing from the field to toolbar controls. **`Textarea`** is `forwardRef` for selection restore after programmatic inserts.
- **`ExercisePreText`** (`components/exercises/exercise-pre-text.tsx`): read-only display on the exercise **detail** page for layer bodies and other long strings; preserves line breaks like pre-wrapped text; lines beginning with `•` get a **hanging indent** so wrapped text aligns under the text after the bullet.

### Database Models (Prisma)
- `Instructor` — identity & auth (mapped as Better Auth's `user` via `user.modelName`); has `role` (`Role` enum: `ADMIN`/`INSTRUCTOR`), `banned`, `banReason`, `banExpires`
- `Session`, `Account`, `Verification` — Better Auth managed tables
- `Invitation` — admin-created invitations with `token`, `status` (`InvitationStatus` enum: `PENDING`/`ACCEPTED`/`EXPIRED`), `role`, `expiresAt`;
- `PlatformSetting` — key-value store for platform config (e.g. `signupEnabled`)
- `ExerciseFolder`, `Exercise`, `ExerciseImage`, `ExerciseLayer` — exercise library; `Exercise` has optional **`progressionOfId`** (easier parent exercise) forming a linear progression chain per instructor; optional **`progressionNotes`** / **`regressionNotes`**; `ExerciseLayer` stores ordered content steps per exercise plus optional **`isFinisher`** on the final layer
- `DropdownCategory`, `DropdownOption` — configurable dropdown menus; categories and global defaults are seeded in `seed.ts` (exercise-related keys plus `class_type` / `class_style`); options can be global (`instructorId` null) or instructor-scoped
- `ClassPlanTemplate`, `PlanSection`, `PlanSectionExercise` — class plan templates
- `Class`, `ClassInstance` — scheduling (GROUP/PRIVATE, recurrence)
- `Client`, `Enrollment`, `Attendance` — client roster
- `SessionNote`, `SessionNoteExercise` — per-instance notes
